1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000
Buying native XRP should not require exposing your price
or trusting a desk to settle.

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:16,000
Cinder is a commit-reveal RFQ market on Flare.
Buyers lock escrow, makers compete with hidden quotes.

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Connect a Coston2 wallet, claim demo liquidity,
then approve and create a real escrow transaction.

4
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Only the quote hash reaches the chain during bidding.
The secret stays in the browser until reveal.

5
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:49,000
The lowest valid quote inside the live FTSOv2 band wins—
without a Cinder operator key.

6
00:00:49,000 --> 00:01:00,000
The winner delivered ten native XRP on XRPL Testnet
with the contract-generated payment reference.

7
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:09,000
FDC verified the destination, amount and reference.
Only then did escrow release ten cUSD.

8
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Cinder makes native XRP safely executable on Flare.
Try the live testnet demo.
